Key trends:
Miniaturization As communications and consumer products become more integrated, miniaturized, and multifunctional, chip varistors are required to be smaller in size
Low Voltage Transient voltage and surge current are fatal to integrated circuits and semiconductor devices, especially in recent years because of the gradual decline of the operating voltage of integrated circuits and semiconductor devices, it is necessary to develop chip varistors with low operating voltage (less than 5 volts).
Integrated Array In order to reduce the volume of chip varistors, several single varistors are integrated into a single electronic component, called a varistor bar.Compared with discrete devices, varistor bars can save space on the board and production and assembly costs.
Multiple Using LTCC technology, the varistor is combined with other components to form a multifunctional composite module, such as varistor and inductor, to form a module with both ESD protection and anti-EMI function.
